column6: Heavy barnacle growth at waterline and bottom of keel. Widespread but light barnacle growth over rest of hull. No others issues observed

Light barnacle growth at waterline. Spots of heavy growth underside of keel and various other spots where paint is missing. There is “paint burn” / “sickness” above the forward starboard thru-hull drain. I advise being mindful of corrosive material being discharged here. Bleach, for instance, will cause this. Also, there is widespread embedded black algae  throughout the paint, indicative of the anti-fouling properties diminishing. Paint wear remains good, save for the areas of missing paint.
Starboard waterline is submerged. Consider raising waterline or redistributing weight aboard. Hard growth occuring on gelcoat above waterline starboard.
